Package: EcoStatusR
Title: Analysis of Ecological and Evolutionary Status
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Imports: Rdpack, ape, dplyr, tidyr, stringr, rgbif, rgl, magrittr, purrr, treeio, vegan, datasets, base, dbscan, foreach, doParallel, sf, tibble, utils
RdMacros: Rdpack
Authors@R: 
    person("Alivia", "Nytko", , "anytko@vols.utk.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4499-4839"))
Description: EcoStatusR calculates measures of range size, evolutionary distinctiveness, and functional trait distinctiveness to classify the ecological status of species varying in geographic, phylogenetic, and functional rarity. Ecological status can be used to infer associated organismal strategy. EcoStatus also allows users to utilize their own data to determine the ecological status of species of interest.
